INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('17453', '10', 'In a blender or food processor, pure remaining 1/2 cup olive oil, the lemon juice, 1/2 cup mint leaves, the garlic, remaining 1/2 tsp. salt, the pepper, and mustard.'),
('17453', '11', 'Drizzle three-fourths of dressing over eggplant. Arrange tomatoes on eggplant, drizzle them with remaining dressing, and top with remaining 1/2 cup mint. Season to taste with more salt.'),
('17453', '12', 'Make ahead: Prepare recipe through step 5 up to 3 hours ahead, cover, and hold at room temperature. Assemble just before serving.'),
('17454', '1', 'In a large bowl, beat egg to blend.'),
('17454', '2', 'Add crab, shrimp, rockfish, bread crumbs, green onions, bell pepper, broth, and mustard. Gently shape mixture into 8 equal patties about 3 inches wide and 3/4 inch thick; set slightly apart on a sheet of waxed paper or foil.'),
('17454', '3', 'Pour 1/2 tablespoon oil into a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add half the crab cakes and cook, turning once, until cakes are browned on both sides and seafood in center of thickest part is opaque but still moist-looking (cut to test), 6 to 8 minutes total. As cakes are cooked, transfer to an ovenproof platter and keep warm in a 200 oven.'),
('17454', '4', 'Add remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil to pan and cook remaining cakes.'),
('17454', '5', 'Serve crab cakes with mandarin chutney and salt and pepper to add to taste.'),
('17454', '6', 'How to cook crab'),
('17454', '7', 'Keep live crabs loosely covered in the refrigerator up to 12 hours. Grasp crabs carefully from the rear end, between the legs, and put in a pan to make sure they fit, with 3 to 4 inches of clearance below pan rim.'),
('17454', '8', 'Remove crabs and fill pan with enough water to cover crabs by 2 to 3 inches. Cover pan and bring water to a boil over high heat.'),
('17454', '9', 'One at a time, grasp crabs as described above and plunge them headfirst into the boiling water; if you have too much water, ladle out excess and discard. Cover pan and start timing. When water resumes boiling, reduce heat to a simmer. Cook 1 1/2- to 2 1/2-pound crabs 15 minutes, 3-pound crabs about 20 minutes.'),
('17454', '10', 'Drain crabs; to be able to handle quickly, rinse briefly with cool water.'),
('17454', '11', 'How to clean, crack, and shell crab'),
('17454', '12', 'Pull off and discard triangular flap from belly side.'),
('17454', '13', 'Turn crab belly side down; pulling from the rear end, lift off back shell.'),
('17454', '14', 'Drain and discard liquid from shell. If desired, scoop soft, golden crab butter and white crab fat from shell into a small bowl to eat by the spoonful with crab or to stir into a dipping sauce. If using back shell for garnish, break bony section (mouth) from front end of shell and discard. Rinse shell well and drain.'),
('17454', '15', 'On the body section, pull off and discard reddish membrane that covers the center (if it hasn''t come off with the back) and any loose pieces. Scoop out any remaining golden butter and add to bowl. Pull off and discard long, spongy gills from sides of body. Rinse body well with cool water.'),
('17454', '16', 'Twist legs and claws from body. Using a nutcracker or wood mallet, crack the shell of each leg and claw section. With a knife, cut the body into quarters.'),
('17454', '17', 'Break apart legs and claws; using your fingers, a small fork, a pick, or a crab leg tip, remove meat. Pull body sections apart and dig out pockets of meat. Discard shells. One cooked, cleaned 1 3/4- to 2-pound crab (with back shell) yields 7 1/2 to 8 ounces (1 1/3 to 1 1/2 cups) of meat; heavier crabs do not always have more meat.'),
('17459', '1', 'Preheat oven to 325°F.'),
('17459', '2', 'Place ham in large roasting pan.'),
('17459', '3', 'Pour apple juice over ham. Cover ham completely with parchment paper, then cover ham and roasting pan completely with heavy-duty foil, sealing tightly at edges of pan.'),
('17459', '4', 'Bake ham until instant-read thermometer inserted into center of ham registers 145°F, about 3 hours 45 minutes.'),
('17459', '5', 'Remove ham from oven. Increase oven temperature to 375°F.'),
('17459', '6', 'Remove foil and parchment from ham.'),
('17459', '7', 'Drain and discard liquids from roasting pan.'),
('17459', '8', 'Cut off rind and all but 1/4-inch-thick layer of fat from ham and discard. Using long sharp knife, score fat in 1-inch-wide, 1/4-inch-deep diamond pattern.'),
('17459', '9', 'Spread mustard evenly over fat layer on ham. Pat brown sugar over mustard coating, pressing firmly to adhere.'),
('17459', '10', 'Drizzle honey evenly over.'),
('17459', '11', 'Bake until ham is well glazed, spooning any mustard and sugar glaze that slides into roasting pan back over ham, about 30 minutes.'),
('17459', '12', 'Transfer ham to serving platter; let cool at least 45 minutes. Slice ham and serve slightly warm or at room temperature.'),
('17468', '1', 'For the Honey Mustard Mayonnaise: Whip the mustard with the honey and the mayonnaise.'),
('17468', '2', 'Add the cream and season with the paprika, salt and freshly grated pepper. Cover and chill.'),
('17468', '3', 'For the Chicken croquettes: Chopp the shallots very finely. Peel the garlic, cut in half, remove the green inside, and chopp very finely.'),
('17468', '4', 'In a saut pan, add the olive oil and the onions and fry until translucid.'),
('17468', '5', 'Add the garlic, fry an extra 1 minute and remove from the heat.'),
('17468', '6', 'Let cool completely.'),
('17468', '7', 'Cut the inside of the bread (without the crust) in small pieces and measure 1 cup. Put in a bowl and add the milk.'),
('17468', '8', 'Mix with your hands until the milk is totally absorbed.'),
('17468', '9', 'Cut the chicken meat in small pieces making sure there are no bones. In a food processor pulse the chicken meat until is ground.'),
('17468', '10', 'Add the mustard, bread with milk, chopped parsley, cooled sauted shallots and garlic, and grated fresh ginger.'),
('17468', '11', 'Add some salt and freshly ground pepper. Pulse until combined. Check the seasoning. Chill for 30 minutes.'),
('17468', '12', 'Beat 1 whole egg in a bowl.'),
('17468', '13', 'Put the breadcrumbs in a plate. Make the croquettes taking some chicken mince and giving them a shape of a cylinder 1 1/2 inches ling by 3/4 inches thick.'),
('17468', '14', 'Roll the croquettes in the egg and then in the bread crumbs. At this point you can chill them and wait until serving time, or freeze them in a tray and when frozen put them in a plastic bag.'),
('17468', '15', 'Heat the oil to medium temperature (the oil should be deep enough to come to half the height of the croquettes). Fry the croquettes slowly as you need to make sure the inside is well cooked. When golden on one side turn them over and continue frying until golden on the other side.'),
('17468', '16', 'Remove from the oil and put on kitchen paper towel to absorb excess oil.'),
('17468', '17', 'Serve with a green salad, mashed potatoes and the Honey Mustard Mayonnaise on the side.'),
('17468', '18', 'The croquettes can also be serve at room temperature for a picnic or made smaller (half the size) and served as finger food.'),
('17469', '1', 'Whisk mustard, olive oil, parsley, and thyme in small bowl to blend. Stir in garlic.'),
('17469', '2', 'Spread mustard mixture generously inside cavities and over outside of chickens.'),
('17469', '3', 'Place chickens in glass baking dish; cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.'),
('17469', '4', 'Let chickens stand at room temperature 30 minutes. Sprinkle chickens generously inside and out with salt and pepper; let stand 30 minutes longer.'),
('17469', '5', 'Preheat oven to 400°F.'),
('17469', '6', 'Place chickens on rack set in large roasting pan. Tie legs together to hold shape.'),
('17469', '7', 'Spread any accumulated mustard marinade from dish over chickens.'),
('17469', '8', 'Place rosemary and sage sprigs atop chickens. Roast chickens until juices run clear when fork is inserted into thickest part of thigh, basting occasionally with pan juices, about 1 hour 10 minutes.'),
('17469', '9', 'Divide Warm Frisée, Fingerling, and Bacon Salad among 6 plates. Carve chickens and arrange atop salad. Spoon some of pan juices over and serve.'),
('17473', '1', 'Melt 1 tablespoon butter with 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('17473', '2', 'Add leeks and cook until beginning to turn golden, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes. Stir in broth, wine, and garlic. Boil until mixture is reduced to 1 2/3 cups, about 4 minutes.'),
('17473', '3', 'Whisk in crème fraîche and mustard; set aside. (Sauce can be made 2 hours ahead.'),
('17473', '4', 'Let stand at room temperature.) Melt 1 tablespoon butter with 1 tablespoon oil in another large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper. Sauté until browned and cooked, about 5 minutes per side.'),
('17473', '5', 'Transfer pork to platter.'),
('17473', '6', 'Add sauce to skillet; simmer sauce over medium heat until slightly thickened, scraping up any browned bits, about 2 minutes. Stir in chopped chives and tarragon. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('17473', '7', 'Return pork to skillet. Cook over medium heat just until rewarmed, stirring frequently, about 1 minute.'),
('17473', '8', 'Transfer to platter, sprinkle with parsley, and serve.'),
('17476', '1', 'In a 5- to 6-quart pan over medium-high heat, stir bacon often until browned and crisp, 6 to 8 minutes. With a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels to drain. Discard all but 1 1/2 tablespoons fat in pan.'),
('17476', '2', 'Add onions to pan and stir often until they begin to brown and stick to bottom of pan, 7 to 9 minutes.'),
('17476', '3', 'Add beans and their liquid, catsup, brown sugar, dry mustard, and cooked bacon; mix well.'),
('17476', '4', 'Pour into a shallow 3-quart casserole.'),
('17476', '5', 'Bake, uncovered, in a 350 regular or convection oven until beans are bubbling in the center, 30 to 40 minutes.'),
('17476', '6', 'Serve hot.'),
('17477', '1', 'Core and halve tomatoes.'),
('17477', '2', 'Remove seeds (either scoop them out with a spoon or hold a half in your hand and squeeze out the seeds) and cut tomatoes into bite-size pieces. Put tomatoes in a large bowl.'),
('17477', '3', 'Remove stem and seeds from chile. Finely chop chile and add to tomatoes. Set aside.'),
('17477', '4', 'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lime juice, 1/2 tsp. salt, and mustard until emulsified.'),
('17477', '5', 'Drizzle dressing over tomatoes and chiles and toss gently to combine.'),
('17477', '6', 'Add more salt to taste if you like.'),
('17477', '7', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('17484', '1', 'Remove and discard skin from ham. Using a boning knife, score fat on ham 1/8" deep in a diamond pattern.'),
('17484', '2', 'Place ham, fat side up, on a lightly greased rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.'),
('17484', '3', 'Stir together preserves, mustard, and 1 cup peach nectar in a large bowl; pour over ham.'),
('17484', '4', 'Bake ham, uncovered, at 350 for 2 hours and 20 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 140, basting with pan juices every 20 minutes.'),
('17484', '5', 'Transfer ham to a serving platter.'),
('17484', '6', 'Let stand 15 minutes before carving.'),
('17484', '7', 'Pour pan drippings into a large saucepan.'),
('17484', '8', 'Add remaining 1 cup peach nectar; bring to a boil.'),
('17484', '9', 'Serve sauce with ham.'),
('17484', '10', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('17488', '1', 'In the bowl of a standing electric mixer fitted with a dough hook, mix 2 tablespoons of the warm water with the yeast and let stand until foamy.'),
('17488', '2', 'Add the remaining 1 1/3 cups of warm water along with the sugar and swirl to dissolve the sugar.'),
('17488', '3', 'Add the flour and mix at medium-low speed until a firm, pliable dough forms.'),
('17488', '4', 'Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead for 2 minutes.'),
('17488', '5', 'Roll the dough into a 2-foot-long sausage.'),
('17488', '6', 'Cut the dough into 20 pieces. Cover with plastic and a damp cloth and let rest for 10 minutes.'),
('17488', '7', 'Roll each piece of dough into a 12-inch-long rope. To form pretzels, shape each rope into a U; cross the two sides of the U over each other, twist and press the ends down on the pretzel. Arrange the pretzels on a lightly floured surface about 1-inch apart and cover with lightly oiled plastic wrap.'),
('17488', '8', 'Let the pretzels rest for 30 minutes.'),
('17488', '9', 'Preheat the oven to 42'),
('17488', '10', 'In a large stockpot, bring the cold water to a boil.'),
('17488', '11', 'Add the baking soda. Carefully slide 5 of the pretzels into the boiling water and boil for 30 seconds, turning once. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the pretzels to a rack to drain right-side up; sprinkle lightly with salt. Repeat with the remaining pretzels, in 3 batches.'),
('17488', '12', 'Lightly oil 2 baking sheets. Arrange the pretzels on the baking sheets and bake on the upper and middle racks of the oven for about 10 minutes, or until browned all over; shift the pans from top to bottom and back to front halfway through if necessary, for even baking.'),
('17488', '13', 'Let the pretzels cool on the baking sheets for about 5 minutes, then transfer them to a rack.'),
('17488', '14', 'Serve warm or at room temperature, with mustard.'),
('17490', '1', 'Combine sugar and vinegar in a 6 quart pot; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.'),
('17490', '2', 'remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, until syrupy and slightly thickened, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir occasionally during cooking.'),
('17491', '1', 'Begin by making the lentils.  Over medium-low heat, sauté the carrots and shallot in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.  Season them with the thyme leaves, salt, and pepper, and cook for 5 minutes, until they are just sweating and soft and fragrant.'),
('17491', '2', 'Add in the lentils, and season again with salt and pepper.'),
('17491', '3', 'Increase the heat to high, and pour in the white wine.  Stir, and cook until the wine is absorbed.'),
('17491', '4', 'Add the stock or water.  Cover, and bring to a boil.  Once the water boils, reduce the heat to low, keep covered, and cook for around 25 minutes, until the lentils are tender, but still have a good bite to them, and hold their shape.'),
('17491', '5', 'Drain out any excess liquid, and toss with the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil, and the parsley.  Adjust seasonings as needed.'),
('17491', '6', 'For the salmon, season the fillets with salt and pepper on both sides, and paint the soft butter on the skin side of the salmon.  Use all of it, even if it looks excessive.  This is what makes the skin so crispy and perfect.'),
('17491', '7', 'Heat a large sauté pan on medium heat, and add the 2 tablespoons olive oil.  When it shimmers, carefully add the salmon, skin side down.  It will splatter a bit, so drop the salmon into the pot slowly, and away from you.  Cook for 5 minutes, then turn over, and cook for 3 minutes, or until you''ve achieved desired doneness.'),
('17491', '8', 'While the salmon cooks, prepare the mustard crème fraîche.  Stir together the crème fraîche, 2 mustards, and lemon zest, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('17491', '9', 'To serve this dish, spoon a mound of the lentils on a plate, and perch the salmon on top.  Spoon the crème fraîche over the hot fish, and let it melt into the filet and into the lentils.'),
('17491', '10', 'Serve more sauce alongside.'),
('17491', '11', 'Garnish with a few lemon slices, some fresh twigs of thyme, and a few mixed olives.'),
('17498', '1', 'Discard center stem from bay leaves, then crumble leaves into grinder and pulse with kosher salt and fennel seeds until bay leaves are finely chopped.'),
('17498', '2', 'Discard any strings from loin if tied. Arrange loin, fat side up, lengthwise on a work surface. Holding knife horizontally, make a lengthwise cut about 1 1/2 inches deep along side of loin (do not cut all the way through). Open loin like a book, then pat dry inside and out. Rub 1 tablespoon mustard all over cut sides, then sprinkle with 1 teaspoon seasoned salt. Close loin and tie crosswise at 1-inch intervals with string. Rub olive oil evenly over roast, then rub with remaining mustard and sprinkle with remaining seasoned salt, pressing lightly to help adhere. Oil roasting rack, then transfer pork, fat side up, to rack set in roasting pan and marinate, loosely covered and chilled, at least 12 hours.'),
('17498', '3', 'Let pork stand at room temperature 30 minutes before roasting.'),
('17498', '4', 'While pork comes to room temperature, put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 450°F.'),
('17498', '5', 'Roast pork 25 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 325°F and continue to roast until thermometer inserted diagonally 2 inches into center of meat registers 145°F, 35 to 45 minutes.'),
('17498', '6', 'Transfer pork to a platter (reserve roasting pan) and let stand, uncovered, 25 minutes.'),
('17499', '1', 'Bring 10 1/2 cups water, coarse salt, honey, lemon juice, lemon peel, bay leaf, and thyme sprigs to boil in large pot. Cool slightly, then refrigerate brine until cold.'),
('17499', '2', 'Place chicken in very large resealable plastic bag; add brine and seal. Refrigerate chicken 6 hours.'),
('17499', '3', 'Drain chicken from brine; rinse and pat dry.'),
('17499', '4', 'Place chicken on plate.'),
('17499', '5', 'Let stand uncovered in refrigerator at least 2 hours and up to 24 hours.'),
('17499', '6', 'Preheat oven to 375°F.'),
('17499', '7', 'Place chicken on rack in roasting pan. Roast chicken 20 minutes; add 1 cup broth to roasting pan. Roast chicken 20 minutes longer; add 1 cup broth to roasting pan. Roast chicken until thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh registers 170°F, about 45 minutes.'),
('17499', '8', 'Let chicken rest 10 minutes.'),
('17499', '9', 'Meanwhile, pour juices from roasting pan into 2-cup measuring cup.'),
('17499', '10', 'Add more broth if needed to equal 2 cups. Simmer butter in medium saucepan over medium heat until beginning to brown, about 2 minutes.'),
('17499', '11', 'Add flour; stir 1 minute.'),
('17499', '12', 'Whisk in broth mixture; bring to boil. Stir in mustard and 1 teaspoon thyme leaves. Season sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('17499', '13', 'Slice chicken. Divide chicken among plates.'),
('17499', '14', 'Drizzle with sauce and serve Green Salad with Olives alongside.'),
('17501', '1', 'Whisk 3 tablespoons olive oil and next 4 ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('17501', '2', 'Arrange green onions, lettuces, and radicchio on baking sheets.'),
('17501', '3', 'Drizzle lightly with oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('17501', '4', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Grill vegetables until beginning to wilt, 1 minute per side for red leaf lettuce, 1 1/2 minutes per side for romaine, 2 minutes per side for green onions, and 3 minutes per side for radicchio.'),
('17501', '5', 'Transfer vegetables to baking sheets.'),
('17501', '6', 'Cut cores from all grilled greens.'),
('17501', '7', 'Cut grilled radicchio crosswise into 1-inch-wide strips.'),
('17501', '8', 'Cut grilled lettuces crosswise into 2-inch-wide strips; chop green onions.'),
('17501', '9', 'Place vegetables in large bowl.'),
('17501', '10', 'Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.'),
('17502', '1', 'Pat chicken dry and season with salt and pepper.'),
('17502', '2', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over high heat until hot but not smoking, then brown chicken well, about 4 minutes on each side.'),
('17502', '3', 'Transfer with tongs to a plate.'),
('17502', '4', 'Add shallots to skillet and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until golden, about 2 minutes. Stir in mustard and coriander seeds, wine, and water and bring to a boil.'),
('17502', '5', 'Return chicken, skin sides up, to skillet and simmer, covered, until chicken is cooked through, 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('17502', '6', 'Transfer chicken to a platter.'),
('17502', '7', 'Add jelly and cilantro to sauce, stirring until jelly is melted. Season sauce with salt and pepper and spoon over chicken.'),
('17505', '1', 'Prepare grill.'),
('17505', '2', 'To prepare sauce, cook bacon in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat 4 minutes or until almost crisp, stirring occasionally.'),
('17505', '3', 'Add chopped onion to pan; cook 4 minutes, stirring frequently.'),
('17505', '4', 'Add mustard and next 5 ingredients (through 1/4 teaspoon ground cumin) to pan, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer for 4 minutes or until slightly thick, stirring occasionally.'),
('17505', '5', 'To prepare pork, combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients (through red pepper) in a small bowl, stirring well; rub mixture evenly over pork.'),
('17505', '6', 'Place pork on grill rack coated with cooking spray. Grill 20 minutes or until a thermometer registers 155 (slightly pink), turning once.'),
('17505', '7', 'Let pork stand 10 minutes.'),
('17505', '8', 'Cut pork crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices.'),
('17505', '9', 'Serve with sauce.'),
('17518', '1', 'Position rack in bottom third of oven and preheat to 325°F.'),
('17518', '2', 'Whisk jelly, mustard, and ginger in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat until melted, about 1 minute.'),
('17518', '3', 'Remove glaze from heat.'),
('17518', '4', 'Trim any tough rind and fat from upper side of ham, leaving 1/4-inch-thick layer of fat. Using long sharp knife, score fat in 1-inch-wide diamond pattern.'),
('17518', '5', 'Place ham in roasting pan.'),
('17518', '6', 'Bake 1 hour.'),
('17518', '7', 'Brush top and sides of ham generously with some of glaze.'),
('17518', '8', 'Bake until thermometer inserted into thickest part of ham registers 140°F, brushing with glaze every 15 minutes and tenting ham with foil if browning too quickly, about 1 hour 15 minutes.'),
('17518', '9', 'Remove ham from oven; let stand 15 minutes.'),
('17518', '10', 'Transfer to platter.'),
('17518', '11', 'Garnish with watercress.'),
('17518', '12', 'Serve with Rhubarb Chutney.'),
('17519', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook mustard seeds, stirring, until they pop and are 1 shade darker, about 2 minutes.'),
('17519', '2', 'Transfer oil with seeds to a large bowl.'),
('17519', '3', 'Simmer vinegar and sugar in a small saucepan, stirring, until sugar is dissolved, then cool 5 minutes.'),
('17519', '4', 'Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in cleaned skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then cook onion, stirring, until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('17519', '5', 'Remove from heat and stir in vinegar, then add to mustard oil in large bowl.'),
('17519', '6', 'Have ready a large bowl of ice and cold water.'),
('17519', '7', 'Cook beans in a pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('17519', '8', 'Drain in a colander and plunge into ice water to stop cooking, then drain well.'),
('17519', '9', 'Toss beans with vinaigrette and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('17519', '10', 'Serve at room temperature or chilled.'),
('17520', '1', 'Bake for 20 minutes until the skin has wrinkled and the eggplant is soft to touch.'),
('17520', '2', 'Remove from the oven and set aside to cool.Grind the spices to form a dry paste.'),
('17520', '3', 'Heat the oil in a large heavy based fry pan; add the ground spices and cook until fragrant, add the garlic and chilli, cook for a further 1-2 minutes.'),
('17520', '4', 'Add the crushed tomatoes and water and bring to the boil.Meanwhile chop the cooled eggplant into 1-2cm cubes.'),
('17520', '5', 'Add the eggplant to the sauce, season with tamarind paste (to taste), reduce heat to low and simmer for 15-20 minutes.'),
('17520', '6', 'Add the fresh mint just before serving and stir through.'),
('17520', '7', 'Place the coconut and sultanas on a baking tray and roast under a medium grill for 1-2 minutes until golden.'),
('17520', '8', 'Serve the curry with steamed basmati rice, topped with coconut and sultanas. Mmmmmmmmmmm'),
('17523', '1', 'In a chilled small, deep bowl, beat cream with a mixer on high speed until cream holds soft peaks.'),
('17523', '2', 'Add mayonnaise, onion, chili sauce, lemon juice, and cayenne to taste.'),
('17523', '3', 'Mix gently. If making ahead, cover and chill dressing up to 4 hours. Stir before serving.'),
('17524', '1', 'Cook sausage in a large skillet over medium-high heat 10 minutes or until browned and thoroughly cooked.'),
('17524', '2', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('17524', '3', 'Divide crescent rolls into individual triangles.'),
('17524', '4', 'Place one cooked sausage link in center of each dough triangle.'),
('17524', '5', 'Roll up, starting at wide end. Arrange on an ungreased baking sheet.'),
('17524', '6', 'Bake 350 for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.'),
('17524', '7', 'Stir together mustard, mayonnaise, and honey.'),
('17524', '8', 'Serve with sausage rolls.'),
('17531', '1', 'To prepare sauce, combine honey and mustard in a small bowl; cover and chill.'),
('17531', '2', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('17531', '3', 'To prepare chicken, combine chicken and buttermilk in a shallow dish; cover and chill 15 minutes.'),
('17531', '4', 'Drain chicken, discarding liquid.'),
('17531', '5', 'Combine cornflakes and next 5 ingredients (cornflakes through pepper) in a large zip-top plastic bag; add 4 chicken pieces to bag. Seal and shake to coat. Repeat procedure with remaining chicken.'),
('17531', '6', 'Spread oil evenly in a jelly-roll pan, and arrange chicken in a single layer in pan.'),
('17531', '7', 'Bake at 400 for 4 minutes on each side or until done.'),
('17531', '8', 'Serve with sauce.'),
('17533', '1', 'Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; pound each to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or small heavy skillet. Sprinkle chicken evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('17533', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('17533', '3', 'Add chicken to pan; cook 4 minutes on each side or until done.'),
('17533', '4', 'Remove chicken from pan.'),
('17533', '5', 'Reduce heat to medium.'),
('17533', '6', 'Add onion to pan; cook 1 minute.'),
('17533', '7', 'Add syrup and remaining ingredients; cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.'),
('17533', '8', 'Serve sauce with chicken.'),
('17541', '1', 'Score the ham by spiraling around it with a knife from top to bottom rotating as you go and then repeat in the other direction forming diamonds with a crisscross pattern about 1 inch apart.'),
('17541', '2', 'Place the ham in a baking dish, insert a meat thermometer, cover in foil and bake in a preheated 250F oven until the temperature reaches 130F, about 2-4 hours depending on the size of the ham.'),
('17541', '3', 'Remove the diamonds with tongs, dab dry with paper towels, brush on the maple syrup followed by the mustard, sprinkle on brown sugar, spritze on the bourbon and press on the gingersnap crumbs.Insert the meat thermometer and bake in a preheated 350F oven until the ham reaches 140F, about 30-60 minutes depending on the size, before letting it rest for 30 minutes and carving it.'),
('17549', '1', 'In a bowl, whisk the mayonnaise, garlic, lemon juice and mustard; season with salt.'),
('17551', '1', 'Stack several snow peas and slice on the diagonal into 1/4-inch-wide strips. Repeat to slice remaining peas.'),
('17551', '2', 'In a large bowl, whisk vegetable oil, soy sauce, sesame oil, ginger, sugar, and mustard until well combined.'),
('17551', '3', 'Add sliced snow peas and 1 tablespoon green onions; mix to coat. Cover and chill until cold, at least 1 hour, or up to 1 day.'),
('17551', '4', 'Just before serving, mound salad on a platter and sprinkle with remaining tablespoon green onions and the sesame seeds.'),
('17554', '1', 'Whisk the mustard, honey, vinegar, and salt and pepper together in a small bowl.'),
('17554', '2', 'Whisking constantly, slowly drizzle in the olive oil. Continue whisking until the vinaigrette thickens. Refrigerate, covered, until 30 minutes before youre ready to use it.'),
('17554', '3', 'Let the vinaigrette come to room temperature before using.'),
('17554', '4', 'var article'),
('17554', '5', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('17554', '6', 'article'),
('17554', '7', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('17556', '1', 'In a large bowl, mix 4 cups cider, 2 cups cold water, 4 tbsp. salt, bay leaves, garlic cloves, and chile flakes.'),
('17556', '2', 'Add pork chops, cover bowl, and chill, turning meat occasionally, at least 3 hours and up to 1 day.'),
('17556', '3', 'Preheat oven to 32'),
('17556', '4', 'Remove pork chops from the brine and blot dry. Melt 2 tbsp. butter in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.'),
('17556', '5', 'Add pork chops (you may need to do this in 2 batches) and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, or until well browned. Flip chops and cook another 3 to 4 minutes, until browned on that side. Layer chops in a 9- by 13-in. baking pan and bake until barely pink in the center (cut to test), 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('17556', '6', 'Meanwhile, pour remaining 3/4 cup cider into the hot frying pan, scraping pan with a wooden spoon to dislodge browned bits.'),
('17556', '7', 'Add the chicken stock, turn the heat to high, and boil until liquid is reduced to about 1/2 cup, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('17556', '8', 'Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 tbsp. butter and the mustard. When sauce is no longer bubbling, stir in crme frache. Season with remaining 1/2 tsp. salt and the pepper.'),
('17556', '9', 'Remove the pork from oven and spoon a generous amount of sauce over each chop.'),
('17556', '10', 'Serve topped with sauted apples.'),
('17560', '1', 'With a slotted spoon, lift pears from poaching liquid; reserve liquid. Slice pears lengthwise or cut them into about 1/2-inch chunks.'),
('17560', '2', 'In a large bowl, combine pears with spinach and macadamia nuts. Coarsely crumble half the cheese over salad.'),
('17560', '3', 'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, rice vinegar, 3 tablespoons reserved pear-poaching liquid (save remaining for another use; see notes), mustard, honey, and thyme.'),
('17560', '4', 'Pour over salad and gently mix to coat, adding salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with pomegranate seeds and crumble remaining cheese over salad.'),
('17560', '5', 'Poached pears: In a 5- to 6-quart pan over medium heat, combine 1 bottle (750 ml.) dry red wine, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 thin strip (3 in. by 1/2 in.) lemon peel (yellow part only), 2 star anise (or 1 teaspoon anise seeds and 1 cinnamon stick, 3 in.), and 1 vanilla bean (6 in.), split lengthwise. Bring to a simmer.'),
('17560', '6', 'Meanwhile, peel 3 firm-ripe Anjou pears (1 1/2 lb. total), cut in half lengthwise, and core.'),
('17560', '7', 'Place pears in wine mixture. Cover and simmer, turning occasionally, until pears are barely tender when pierced, about 15 minutes.'),
('17560', '8', 'Remove from heat and let pears cool in liquid, turning occasionally, at least 30 minutes, or cover and chill up to 3 days.'),
('17561', '1', 'Whisk vinegar and mustard in small bowl. Gradually whisk in olive oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.)'),
('17561', '2', 'Cook fava beans in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 2 minutes.'),
('17561', '3', 'Transfer to bowl of ice water to cool.'),
('17561', '4', 'Drain and peel (if using fresh).'),
('17561', '5', 'Transfer to paper towels to dry.'),
('17561', '6', 'Place fava beans, radishes, herbs, and dressing in medium bowl; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('17561', '7', 'Let salad stand at room temperature at least 20 minutes and up to 1 hour.'),
('17561', '8', 'Melt butter with canola oil in heavy large skillet over high heat. Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper.'),
('17561', '9', 'Add steaks to skillet and cook to desired doneness, about 4 minutes per side for medium-rare.'),
('17561', '10', 'Transfer to cutting board; let stand 10 minutes.'),
('17561', '11', 'Cut each steak into 3 slices.'),
('17561', '12', 'Divide salad among 4 plates. Arrange 1 sliced steak atop each salad. Sprinkle some of cheese over each and serve.'),
('17565', '1', 'Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('17565', '2', 'Place the onions in skillet and cook for 5 minutes.'),
('17565', '3', 'Add the jalapeos, garlic, ginger, and 4 tablespoons of the lemon juice and cook for 5 minutes more.'),
('17565', '4', 'Transfer the mixture to a plate.'),
('17565', '5', 'Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil to skillet and raise heat to medium-high.'),
('17565', '6', 'Add the chicken and stir-fry until golden, about 8 minutes.'),
('17565', '7', 'Add the cayenne, coriander, cumin, mustard seeds, and salt and stir-fry for 2 minutes more.'),
('17565', '8', 'Add the peaches, onion mixture, and 1/2 cup water and simmer for 8 minutes. Stir in the coconut milk, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer gently for 2 minutes. Taste and add the remaining lemon juice, if necessary.'),
('17565', '9', 'Serve with the yogurt, flat bread, or both, if desired.'),
('17572', '1', 'Stir lemon juice into a large bowl of cold water.'),
('17572', '2', 'Peel Jerusalem artichokes and cut into 1/2-inch-thick rounds.'),
('17572', '3', 'Transfer as cut to acidulated water (to prevent discoloring).'),
('17572', '4', 'Bring vinegar, sugar, water, mustard seeds, turmeric, cayenne, and 1 1/2 tsp salt to a boil in a medium nonreactive saucepan, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Cool brine to room temperature.'),
('17572', '5', 'Cook Jerusalem artichokes and onion in a large pot of boiling water 1 minute.'),
('17572', '6', 'Drain and spread out on a kitchen towel to cool. Put vegetables in a glass or ceramic bowl and pour brine over them. Weight vegetables with a small plate to keep submerged, then cover bowl tightly. Chill, stirring once or twice a day, at least 1 week (to allow flavors to develop).'),
('17581', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Butter 8x8x2-inch glass baking dish. Cook macaroni in medium pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.'),
('17581', '2', 'Drain macaroni and place in large bowl.'),
('17581', '3', 'Add butter and toss until melted.'),
('17581', '4', 'Mix in 2 cups cheddar cheese. Beat milk, eggs, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and cayenne pepper in medium bowl to blend. Stir egg mixture into macaroni.'),
('17581', '5', 'Transfer to prepared dish; sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheddar cheese over.'),
('17581', '6', 'Bake macaroni until golden on top and set in center, about 1 hour.'),
('17598', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 45'),
('17598', '2', 'In a large saucepan, cover the eggs with water, add the vinegar and bring to a rapid boil. Cover the saucepan and remove it from the heat; let stand for 15 minutes.'),
('17598', '3', 'Drain the eggs and cool them under cold running water, shaking the pan vigorously to crack the shells.'),
('17598', '4', 'Let the eggs cool in the water.'),
('17598', '5', 'Meanwhile, quarter the bread slices on the diagonal and arrange them in a single layer on a large cookie sheet. Toast the bread in the oven for about 6 minutes, turning once, until barely browned.'),
('17598', '6', 'Shell the eggs and halve them lengthwise. Coarsely chop half of the egg whites and transfer them to a large bowl.'),
('17598', '7', 'Add the remaining whites and all of the yolks to a food processor along with the mayonnaise and mustard and process until smooth. Scrape the mixture into the bowl and blend with the chopped egg whites. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('17598', '8', 'Top the toast points with the egg spread and dust lightly with paprika. Arrange the toasts on a platter and serve. Alternatively, serve the egg spread in a bowl with the toast points alongside.'),
('17602', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Bring vinegar and mustard seeds to boil in small saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer until almost dry, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.'),
('17602', '2', 'Transfer to large bowl.'),
('17602', '3', 'Add Dijon mustard and coriander. Season with coarse salt and pepper.'),
('17602', '4', 'Place potatoes in large saucepan; add water to cover by 1 inch; sprinkle with coarse salt. Boil 3 minutes.'),
('17602', '5', 'Drain; return to pan. Cook over medium-high heat until dry, shaking pan occasionally, 3  minutes.'),
('17602', '6', 'Meanwhile, drizzle 6 tablespoons oil over large rimmed baking sheet.'),
('17602', '7', 'Place sheet in oven 10 minutes to heat.'),
('17602', '8', 'Add potatoes to mustard mixture; toss.'),
('17602', '9', 'Spread potatoes on hot baking sheet (oil may splatter). Sprinkle with coarse salt and pepper. Roast 15 minutes. Turn potatoes; roast until browned and tender, about 15 minutes longer. Season with coarse salt and pepper and serve hot.'),
('17612', '1', 'Combine first 10 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring until well blended. Gently fold in crabmeat. Form mixture into 8 crab cakes (about 1/3 cup each). Cover and chill 1 hour or until ready to cook.'),
('17612', '2', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook crab cakes (in batches, if necessary) 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.'),
('17612', '3', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('17614', '1', 'Slice green onions long and on the bias so you have pieces similar in shape to the cabbage. Toss together onions, cabbages, and cilantro in a large bowl.'),
('17614', '2', 'Zest both limes and juice 1 lime. In a bowl, mix lime zest and juice, yogurt, sugar, salt, and pepper.'),
('17614', '3', 'Pour dressing over cabbage mixture; stir to combine.'),
('17616', '1', 'Whisk together the lime juice, vinegar, chili oil, mayonnaise and soy sauce in a large bowl.'),
('17616', '2', 'Add the cabbage, peppers, snow peas and scallions and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to meld.'),
('17622', '1', 'Heat grill to high (450 to 550).'),
('17622', '2', 'Mix cabbage, 1/4 cup green onions, the vinegar, 1 tsp. each garlic and ginger, 2 tsp. sesame oil, and 1/2 tsp. chili sauce in a large bowl. Set relish aside, stirring occasionally. In another bowl, mix mayonnaise with remaining 1 tsp. chili sauce.'),
('17622', '3', 'Combine beef, soy sauce, and remaining 1/4 cup green onions, 1 tbsp. each garlic and ginger, and 1 tsp. sesame oil. Shape into 4 patties, each about 1/2 in. thick.'),
('17622', '4', 'Oil cooking grate, using tongs and a wad of oiled paper towels. Grill burgers, covered, turning once, 7 to 8 minutes total for medium. In the final minutes, toast buns.'),
('17622', '5', 'Spread bun bottoms with chili mayonnaise. Set burgers on buns. With a slotted spoon, put some cabbage relish on each.'),
('17622', '6', 'Serve with remaining relish.'),
('17622', '7', 'Shortcut: Omit the relish and use kimchi from the refrigerated section of a supermarket or Asian market; the recipe will be saltier.'),
('17626', '1', 'In a salad bowl, combine cabbage, spinach, strawberries, and green onions.'),
('17626', '2', 'In a 3-quart pan over medium-low heat, stir almonds often until golden, 5 to 8 minutes.'),
('17626', '3', 'Pour from pan.'),
('17626', '4', 'Add sesame oil, vinegar, ginger, garlic, soy sauce, five spice, and chile flakes to pan. Stir often over low heat until bubbling, 30 seconds.'),
('17626', '5', 'Pour dressing and almonds over salad and mix gently.'),
('17627', '1', 'Cook vermicelli according to package directions.'),
('17627', '2', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('17627', '3', 'Meanwhile, heat oil in a large pot over medium heat.'),
('17627', '4', 'Add tofu; cook until browned, 2 minutes.'),
('17627', '5', 'Add garlic and ginger and cook about 2 minutes.'),
('17627', '6', 'Add mushrooms, broth, and cabbage and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in reserved noodles. Ladle soup into bowls and add cilantro, onions, and soy sauce.'),
('17633', '1', 'Soak noodles in hot water 10 minutes; drain and set aside.'),
('17633', '2', 'Saut diced onion in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until tender.'),
('17633', '3', 'Add carrot and next 4 ingredients; cook, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.'),
('17633', '4', 'Stir together broth and cornstarch until smooth; add to chicken mixture.'),
('17633', '5', 'Add soy sauce and oyster sauce; bring mixture to a boil, and cook 1 minute.'),
('17633', '6', 'Remove from heat; serve over noodles.'),
('17633', '7', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('17634', '1', 'Stir together flavor packet from ramen noodle soup mix, 2 cups water, chopped green onion, and chopped fresh cilantro in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil; add noodles and snow peas. Cook 1 minute, and stir in shrimp. Cook 2 minutes.'),
('17634', '2', 'Transfer to a bowl, and top with shredded cabbage and chopped peanuts.'),
('17634', '3', 'Note: You can substitute 1/2 cup chopped cooked chicken for the shrimp.'),
('17640', '1', 'Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice, stirring well; cover and chill.'),
('17640', '2', 'Gently toss together cabbage and remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Carefully toss in dressing.'),
('17640', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
('17645', '1', 'Put the flour in a medium bowl.'),
('17645', '2', 'Add the water in a steady stream, stirring until a raggy dough forms. Turn the dough out on a work surface and knead until smooth, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle the dough with flour, cover loosely with plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.'),
('17645', '3', 'In a large bowl, knead the chicken with the cabbage, cilantro, lemongrass, chives, ginger, garlic and egg and salt.'),
('17645', '4', 'Line a baking sheet with wax paper and dust with flour. Quarter the dumpling dough. On a lightly floured work surface, roll each piece of dough into a 12-inch rope.'),
('17645', '5', 'Cut each rope into 12 pieces and roll into balls; sprinkle with flour. Working with 5 or 6 balls at a time, roll to 3 1/2-inch rounds.'),
('17645', '6', 'Brush the excess flour off of the rounds. Spoon 1 tablespoon of the filling onto the center of each round. Bring up the sides of the wrapper; press and pleat the edges to seal in the filling. Lift each dumpling by the pleated edge, transfer to the baking sheet and press down lightly to flatten. Repeat with the remaining dough.'),
('17645', '7', 'In a very large nonstick skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil. Arrange half of the dumplings in the pan, pleated edge up. Cook over high heat until the bottoms are lightly browned, about 2 minutes.'),
('17645', '8', 'Add 1/2 cup of water to the skillet, cover and cook until the water is evaporated and the dumplings are cooked through, about 5 minutes longer. Uncover and cook until the bottoms are well browned, about 1 minute longer.'),
('17645', '9', 'Transfer the dumplings to a plate. Cook the remaining dumplings in the remaining oil and serve.'),
('17648', '1', 'Whisk together lemon juice, zest, sugar, salt, and pepper until sugar is dissolved, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified.'),
('17648', '2', 'Just before serving, toss cabbage, parsley, and radicchio in a large bowl with just enough dressing to coat, then season with salt and pepper.'),
('17650', '1', 'On a work surface, chop the shrimp and scallions.'),
('17650', '2', 'Transfer to a large bowl and add the sambal mayonnaise, cabbage, water chestnuts, cilantro and carrot; season lightly with salt and pepper. Mound the shrimp salad on the ciabatta rolls, close the sandwiches and serve.'),
('17651', '1', 'In a large bowl, mix the mayonnaise, mirin, rice vinegar, soy sauce, lemon juice and jalapeo.'),
('17651', '2', 'Add the red and napa cabbages, carrot, jicama, daikon, cucumber, scallions and bean sprouts, season with salt and toss well; serve.'),
('17652', '1', 'Whisk together first 8 ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('17652', '2', 'Combine chicken and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('17652', '3', 'Add dressing, tossing to coat.'),
('17652', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('17653', '1', 'Light a grill or heat a grill pan. In a medium bowl, toss the shrimp with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill, turning once, until the shrimp are pink and curled, about 5 minutes.'),
('17653', '2', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('17653', '3', 'Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a medium skillet.'),
('17653', '4', 'Add the corn and cook over moderately high heat until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.'),
('17653', '5', 'Transfer to a bowl and let cool.'),
('17653', '6', 'Add the celery, lemon juice, garlic, mayonnaise, paprika and cayenne and season with salt and pepper. Stir in the shredded cabbage.'),
('17653', '7', 'Quickly warm the tortillas on the grill.'),
('17653', '8', 'Spread the tortillas on a work surface and mound the corn slaw in the center of each. Top with the shrimp.'),
('17653', '9', 'Roll up the wraps, cut in half and serve.'),
('17656', '1', 'Preheat the broiler. Peel the membrane from the underside of the ribs and place them, skinned side up, on 2 rimmed baking sheets. Broil the ribs 6 inches from the heat, turning once, until browned on both sides, 8 to 10 minutes per sheet.'),
('17656', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('17656', '3', 'In a small bowl, mix the lemon zest with 2 tablespoons of the parsley and the chives, tarragon and thyme.'),
('17656', '4', 'Brush the ribs with some of the Ham Hock Stock over the ribs and sprinkle with half of the herb mixture. Season the ribs with salt and pepper and bake for about 1 hour, without turning, until very tender; baste the ribs with the stock and sprinkle with the herb mixture several times while baking.'),
('17656', '5', 'Transfer the ribs to a cutting board and cut into individual ribs.'),
('17656', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk the oil with the vinegar and season with salt and pepper.'),
('17656', '7', 'Add the cabbage, apples and the remaining 2 tablespoons of chopped parsley and toss to coat.'),
('17656', '8', 'Serve with the ribs.'),
('17661', '1', 'In a bowl, mix turkey, egg, mushrooms, cabbage, water chestnuts, green onions, cornstarch, ginger, 3 tablespoons soy sauce, oyster sauce, wine, salt, sugar, and pepper until well blended.'),
('17661', '2', 'To assemble each dumpling, fill a small bowl with water.'),
('17661', '3', 'Place one wrapper on a flat surface; cover remaining wrappers with plastic wrap to keep pliable.'),
('17661', '4', 'Place a scant tablespoon of filling in center of wrapper. With your fingers, moisten edge of wrapper all the way around with water, then bring opposite sides together over filling and pinch edges together only in the center. On front side of dumpling, make two pleats on each side of center, folding to the center, and press all edges to seal. Set dumpling, seam side up so dumpling sits flat, on a lightly floured baking sheet. Cover with plastic wrap while you fill remaining wrappers (see notes).'),
('17661', '5', 'To cook each batch, set a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat (see notes). When hot, coat pan bottom with 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Set dumplings, seam up and slightly apart, in a single layer in pan. Cook until bottoms are golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('17661', '6', 'Add 1/3 cup water, cover pan tightly, reduce heat to medium-low, and cook until filling is no longer pink in the center (cut to test), 3 to 6 minutes (10 to 11 minutes if frozen). Uncover and, if there is still liquid in pan, continue cooking over medium-high heat until the liquid has evaporated.'),
('17661', '7', 'Using a wide spatula, transfer dumplings to a heatproof platter.'),
('17661', '8', 'Serve, or cover and keep warm in a 200 oven. Repeat to cook remaining dumplings.'),
('17661', '9', 'Serve with soy sauce, rice vinegar, and chili oil for dipping.'),
('17663', '1', 'In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil.'),
('17663', '2', 'Add the shrimp and stir-fry over moderately high heat until curled, 2 minutes; transfer to a plate.'),
('17663', '3', 'Add 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil to the skillet.'),
('17663', '4', 'Add the chicken and stir-fry until white throughout, 3 minutes; transfer to the plate with the shrimp.'),
('17663', '5', 'Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to the skillet.'),
('17663', '6', 'Add the cabbage, onion, carrot and the mushrooms and stir-fry for 4 minutes.'),
('17663', '7', 'Add the stock, soy sauce, sesame oil, shrimp and chicken; remove from the heat.'),
('17663', '8', 'Meanwhile, cook the udon in a pot of boiling salted water for 1 minute.'),
('17663', '9', 'Drain and add to the skillet. Stir-fry over high heat until heated through. Season with salt and pepper, garnish with scallions and serve.'),
('17667', '1', 'Toss the cabbage, radicchio, red onion, and chives in a large bowl.'),
('17667', '2', 'In a separate bowl, mix the buttermilk, sour cream, honey, Dijon mustard, vinegar, salt, and pepper together.'),
('17667', '3', 'Add the dressing to the cabbage mixture and toss to coat.'),
('17667', '4', 'Let marinate in the refrigerator for an hour before serving.'),
('17668', '1', 'Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.'),
('17668', '2', 'Stir together flavor packet from noodles and chicken broth in a 3-qt. saucepan. Bring to a boil; add shrimp, and cook 3 minutes. Stir in Szechuan sauce and next 3 ingredients. Cook 2 minutes. Stir in noodles, cilantro, and green onions.'),
('17668', '3', 'Note: We tested with Annie Chun''s All Natural Asian Cuisine Teriyaki Meal Starter and House of Tsang Szechuan Spicy Stir Fry Sauce.'),
('17670', '1', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('17670', '2', 'Add almonds; saut 1 minute.'),
('17670', '3', 'Add noodles; saut 3 minutes or until almonds and noodles are toasted. Set aside.'),
('17670', '4', 'Combine soy sauce and next 6 ingredients (through chile paste) in a large bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('17670', '5', 'Add cabbages, chicken, and cilantro; toss gently to coat. Top with oranges and almond mixture.'),
('17677', '1', 'In a large, deep skillet, heat the oil.'),
('17677', '2', 'Add the garlic, shallots, chiles, lemongrass and ginger and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the aromatics are softened and golden, about 5 minutes.'),
('17677', '3', 'Add the brown sugar and coriander and cook until the sugar is melted, about 20 seconds.'),
('17677', '4', 'Add the coconut milk and simmer, stirring, for 2 minutes.'),
('17677', '5', 'Transfer to a food processor and blend until pureed. Blend in the lime juice and fish sauce. Scrape the sauce into a glass measuring cup and season with salt and pepper. Leave the skillet on the stove.'),
('17677', '6', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('17677', '7', 'Add the snow peas and blanch until bright green, about 40 seconds. Using a slotted spoon, transfer them to a plate to cool.'),
('17677', '8', 'Add the noodles to the pot and cook, stirring, until al dente.'),
('17677', '9', 'Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water.'),
('17677', '10', 'Add 1 cup of the curry sauce to the skillet and bring to a simmer over moderate heat.'),
('17677', '11', 'Add the noodles, snow peas, red pepper, cabbage and carrot and toss well to thoroughly coat the noodles with the sauce.'),
('17677', '12', 'Add some of the reserved cooking water if the noodles seem dry. Season with salt and pepper and serve right away.'),
('17679', '1', 'Stir together first 6 ingredients and 1/4 cup cilantro in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('17679', '2', 'Let stand 10 minutes.'),
('17679', '3', 'Stir together mayonnaise, sriracha, and remaining 1/4 cup cilantro.'),
('17679', '4', 'Spread buns with mayonnaise mixture. Top bottom halves of buns with bacon, tomatoes, and cabbage mixture. Cover with top halves of buns, mayonnaise mixture sides down.'),
('17680', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('17680', '2', 'Stir together first 5 ingredients.'),
('17680', '3', 'Spread in a single layer on a 15- x 10-inch jelly-roll pan.'),
('17680', '4', 'Bake at 450 for 13 to 15 minutes or until just tender and lightly browned. Cool 20 minutes.'),
('17680', '5', 'Combine roasted vegetables, cabbage, and next 3 ingredients. Chill 30 minutes to 4 hours. Stir just before serving.'),
('17682', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('17682', '2', 'Whisk together soy sauce and 1/4 cup dressing in a large shallow dish or zip-top plastic freezer bag; add pork, turning to coat. Cover or seal, and chill 10 minutes, turning once.'),
('17682', '3', 'Meanwhile, combine cabbage, next 3 ingredients, and remaining 1/4 cup dressing. Cover and chill until ready to serve.'),
('17682', '4', 'Remove pork from marinade, discarding marinade.'),
('17682', '5', 'Place pork on a lightly greased aluminum foil-lined baking sheet.'),
('17682', '6', 'Bake at 450 for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.'),
('17682', '7', 'Remove from oven, and let stand 5 minutes before slicing.'),
('17682', '8', 'Toss slaw with almonds; serve with pork.'),
('17682', '9', 'Note: We tested with Maple Grove Farms of Vermont All Natural Sesame Ginger Dressing and Blue Diamond Bold Wasabi & Soy Sauce Almonds.'),
('17685', '1', 'In a small shallow bowl, combine the hoisin sauce, sambal oelek, ginger, garlic, wine and 2 tablespoons of the scallions.'),
('17685', '2', 'Add the pork tenderloin and turn to coat with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.'),
('17685', '3', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('17685', '4', 'Drain the pork and season all over with salt.'),
('17685', '5', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large ovenproof skillet until shimmering.'),
('17685', '6', 'Add the pork and cook over high heat until browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('17685', '7', 'Transfer the skillet to the oven and roast the tenderloin for about 10 minutes for medium doneness.'),
('17685', '8', 'Let the pork rest for 15 minutes, then slice thinly.'),
('17685', '9', 'In a large bowl, stir the remaining 1/4 cup of oil with the lemon juice, sugar and crushed red pepper until the sugar is dissolved.'),
('17685', '10', 'Add the cabbage, carrots, basil and the remaining 1/4 cup of scallions. Season with salt and pepper and toss.'),
('17685', '11', 'Assemble the sandwiches on the rolls with the pork slices on the bottom and the slaw mounded on top and serve.'),
('17688', '1', 'Combine cabbage and radishes in a large bowl; set aside.'),
('17688', '2', 'Combine rice vinegar, soy sauce, 1 teaspoon oil, and red pepper, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('17688', '3', 'Heat remaining 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle scallops with salt and black pepper.'),
('17688', '4', 'Add scallops to pan; cook 3 minutes on each side or until done. Arrange 1 cup cabbage mixture on each of 4 plates; top each serving with 4 scallops.'),
('17688', '5', 'Drizzle each serving with 1 tablespoon vinegar mixture; sprinkle each serving with 1/2 teaspoon sesame seeds.'),
('17688', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('17689', '1', 'In a medium bowl, whisk the peanut butter with the lime juice, fish sauce, water, sugar, garlic and Sriracha.'),
('17689', '2', 'In a large bowl, toss the napa and red cabbages with the carrots, peppers, cilantro and mint. Toss the salad with the dressing and season with salt and pepper.'),
('17689', '3', 'Serve right away.'),
('17693', '1', 'Toss beef with 1 tsp. each soy sauce and sesame oil and cook, stirring, over medium heat in a small saucepan. Set aside.'),
('17693', '2', 'Put stock, 1 tbsp. soy sauce, and 2 tsp. sesame oil in a large, heavy pot.'),
('17693', '3', 'Add fermented soybean paste (if using Japanese red miso instead, add just before serving) and stir to dissolve. Stir in garlic and chiles and bring to a boil, covered.'),
('17693', '4', 'Add tofu, cabbage, zucchini, daikon, and two-thirds of the green onions; return to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, covered, until everything is tender, at least 5 minutes. Meanwhile, if using Japanese red miso, whisk with 1/2 cup hot broth. Stir miso broth, remaining green onions, and reserved beef into stew just before serving.'),
('17693', '5', '*Find at Korean markets. Japanese akamiso is available at gourmet grocery stores; you could also use white miso in a pinch.'),
('17712', '1', 'Place cabbage and salt in a large bowl, tossing gently to combine. Weigh down cabbage with another bowl.'),
('17712', '2', 'Let stand at room temperature 3 hours, tossing occasionally.'),
('17712', '3', 'Drain and rinse with cold water.'),
('17712', '4', 'Drain and squeeze dry.'),
('17712', '5', 'Combine cabbage, sesame seeds, and remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.'),
('17719', '1', 'Cover large plate with cabbage.'),
('17719', '2', 'Arrange bacon, vegetables and oranges in rows over cabbage.'),
('17719', '3', 'Mix dressing and soy sauce; drizzle over salad.'),
('17720', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('17720', '2', 'In a saucepan, combine the 2 vinegars and bring to a boil.'),
('17720', '3', 'Put the celery and carrots in a heatproof bowl and pour the vinegar over the vegetables.'),
('17720', '4', 'Let stand until cool. Stir in the peppers and refrigerate until cold, 20 minutes.'),
('17720', '5', 'Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of the vinegar from the vegetables; reserve it for another use.'),
('17720', '6', 'Add the peach, cucumber, frise, arugula and cabbage to the bowl.'),
('17720', '7', 'Drizzle the salad with the olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss.'),
('17720', '8', 'Add the goat cheese and almonds and toss gently. Top the salad with the egg slices, sprinkle with smoked paprika and serve.'),
('17721', '1', 'Crush noodles, place them in a medium skillet and brown in butter over medium heat.'),
('17721', '2', 'Add almonds and sesame seeds.  Stir often to prevent burning.'),
('17721', '3', 'Add seasoning mix from noodles and cool. Toss in a large bowl with cabbage and onions.'),
('17721', '4', 'Prepare the dressing by whisking together the vegetable oil, rice vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil and sugar.'),
('17721', '5', 'Pour over salad, toss and serve.'),
('17729', '1', 'Place tofu on paper towel-lined plate. Top with second paper towel and place plate on top. Allow to drain for 15 minutes. With your fingers, break up the tofu until it resembles crumbled feta cheese.'),
('17729', '2', 'In a small saucepan, bring 1 quart water to a boil and remove from heat.'),
('17729', '3', 'Add noodles, cover, and let steep until noodles are softened, about 5 minutes. Finely chop noodles (you should have about 1/2 cup chopped noodles).'),
('17729', '4', 'Combine tofu, noodles, kimchi, egg, soy sauce, and sesame oil in small bowl. Stir with fork to combine.'),
('17729', '5', 'To fill dumplings, place approximately 2 teaspoons of filling in center of single wrapper. Moisten with wet finger tip, then fold over and seal by crimping edges. Set formed dumpling on rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Keep unfilled wrappers under damp kitchen towel to prevent drying. Note: Formed dumplings at this stage can be stored covered in refrigerator for up to 1 day. For long term storage, freeze dumplings on tray (don''t allow them to tough during freezing or they''ll stick together), remove once frozen, and store in freezer in zipper-lock freezer bag for up to 3 months.'),
('17729', '6', 'To cook, bring 3 quarts water to a rolling boil in a stock pot.'),
('17729', '7', 'Add dupmling ans boil until the skins are just translucent, 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('17729', '8', 'Remove dumplings from water with slotted spoon or spider and serve immediately with soy sauce and vinegar, if desired.'),
('17731', '1', 'Ingredients:for the duck:1 6 lb duckzest of one lemon2 tablespoons five spice powder1 1/2 tablespoons ginger powder1 1/2 tablespoons salt1 tablespoon dark brown sugar1/2 tablespoon freshly ground black pepperfor the filling:1/3 cup dried tiger lily buds6 dried cloud ear mushrooms5 dried black or shiitake mushrooms2 cloves garlic, minced1 carrot, cut into matchsticks1 bunch green onions, cut into 1 inch chunks4 cups shredded napa cabbage1/2 cup chicken or duck stock2 tablespoons shaoxing wine2 tablespoons soy sauce1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with an equal amount of water1 1/2 teaspoon sesame oilfor the omelet:2 eggs1/4 teaspoon sesame oil1/4 cup diced green onionfor the pancakes:2 cups flour3/4 cup boiling watersesame oil'),
